title: For Sale/Trade:  CAI VZ58/2008 with Czech wood kit (Rare)
location: Dupage County IL, Illinois, United States
postcontent: Well, the build is done and it's time for me to move on to another. For those not familiar with this platform, it is sweet! Lighter than a AK47, milled receiver, last round bolt hold open, the list gose on. What you get, the rifle which has been fitted with a nice surplus Czech wood kit, original surplus wood handle bayonet with scabbard, CNC Warrior brake, the original bever barf furniture (top handguard fitted to surplus gray metal), original folding stock, cleaning kit, two mags, and black sling. I was fortunate enough to find fixed stock metal that matches the original finish perfect! Another nice feature I did was tabbed the bolt carrier. While there has been debate lately for the need of this on newer CAI builds, I figured it to be cheap insurance. Research VZ58 trigger gremlin and you will see why this modification is very important. Round count at this point is 0! I will be putting 20 rounds down range with it to test the carrier before it leaves my possession, that's it. I like to make sure there is no problem with the work I do. I would also recommend shooting it with the included bever barf upper handguard in place to preserve the wood one. I'm asking 750.00 for everything. Any questions please ask! Bipod not included. postcontent:
I am sick of people driving up the price of .22 ammo by buying at WalMart and reselling!
I bought 3 boxes of Federal 325 round bulk the other day and they still had about 10 boxes on the shelf for $15.95 a box. Wake Up! The shortage has been caused by opportunists. I was in a store one day when I overheard a guy say "i want all of your 9mm, 380, 45, 223 and any .22 you have.
Someone asked him what he was going to do with all that ammo and without hesitation he said he would resell it and make a ton of money! These guys are not 2nd amendment supporters or sportsmen they are scammers and opportunists. I'm sick of people promoting fear to make money. After 40 years as an FFl and shooter I refuse to support these characters. I'm not opposed to profit but i am opposed to people who could care less about the sport and only seek UNREASONABLE profit! Don't get sucked into these deals and suddenly ammo will be available at reasonable prices again. I can wait!
